{"ts": "2026-06-12T03:40:13.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L3 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l3", "tokens_in": 1782, "tokens_out": 61575, "elapsed_ms": 765653, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level 3 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks for dynamic agent creation.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce — ALWAYS include the user's exact request at the top\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\n## Critical Rules\n- Each subtask description MUST begin with \"USER REQUEST: <exact user task text>\" — this prevents worker hallucination\n- Each subtask must be focused, self-contained, with explicit output file names\n- Never create duplicate task_ids — each worker name must be unique\n- For simple tasks, 3-4 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- Always include a \"tester\" as the FINAL subtask — running test_report.json validation\n- Specify exact file names each worker must produce (e.g. \"Write to styles.css\", \"Write to app.js\")\n- Workers receive NO prior context beyond their subtask description — be thorough in the description\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences, no extra text\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nBuild a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\n\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\n- Add a data-theme=\"dark\" or data-theme=\"light\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\n\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\n- Sections should animate in staggered — each section appears as the user scrolls to it\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\n\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\n### Navbar (sticky)\n- Logo text \"Dashflow\" on the left\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\n\n### Hero\n- Large headline \"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\"\n- Subheadline \"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\"\n- CTA button \"Get Started Free\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\n\n### Features (3 cards)\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \"Real-Time Analytics\", description about live dashboards\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \"Enterprise Security\", description about data protection\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \"Lightning Fast\", description about performance\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\n\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\n- Projects: 12,500+ — Users: 8,200+ — Uptime: 99.9% — Awards: 24\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\n\n### Testimonials (carousel)\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when user hovers the carousel\n\n### Pricing (3 tiers)\n- Starter: $9/mo — Pro (recommended): $29/mo — Enterprise: $99/mo\n- Pro card should have a highlighted border and \"Most Popular\" badge\n- Cards have equal height and center-align\n- Hover: slight scale(1.02) with box-shadow increase\n\n### Newsletter + Footer\n- Email input + Subscribe button\n- Validate email format on submit (regex check for @ and .)\n- Invalid email: show red border + shake animation (CSS @keyframes horizontal shake)\n- Valid email: clear input, show green \"Subscribed!\" toast notification that fades out after 3s\n- Footer: copyright, 3 columns of placeholder links, social media icon placeholders (emoji)\n\n## 4. RESPONSIVE DESIGN\n- Mobile (375px): single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards\n- Tablet (768px): 2-column features, stats in 2x2 grid\n- Desktop (1280px+): 3-column features, stats in a row, full navbar\n- Use CSS Grid + Flexbox, media queries at 768px and 1024px\n\n## 5. CRITICAL RULES\n- Everything in ONE index.html file with linked styles.css and app.js\n- ALL CSS classes must have semantic names matching their section (class=\"hero\", class=\"features\", class=\"stats\", class=\"testimonials\", class=\"pricing\", class=\"newsletter\")\n- JavaScript MUST reference real DOM elements that exist in the HTML\n- The theme toggle MUST actually change the visual appearance — test both themes\n- Do NOT use any external libraries, CDNs, or frameworks — pure HTML/CSS/JS only\n\nFor frontend tasks, you MUST follow these constraints:\n- Always include a final \"integration\" subtask that merges all content/fragments into index.html\n- Always include a \"tester\" subtask as the VERY LAST subtask\n- Good decomposition: [content, html_structure, styling, interactivity, integration, tester]\n- Bad decomposition: [hero_builder, features_builder, cta_builder] — these create standalone pages\n- Each subtask description MUST include the user's verbatim request text at the top\n- Section subtasks produce content fragments into shared files, NOT standalone HTML files\n- The pipeline produces ONE web page: index.html + styles.css + app.js\n\n## CSS-HTML Coordination\n- The HTML worker MUST add semantic CSS classes to every major section (class=\"hero\", class=\"features\", class=\"cta\", class=\"footer\" etc.)\n- The styling worker's subtask MUST say: \"read_file('index.html') FIRST. Write CSS selectors matching the EXACT classes/IDs/elements found in index.html. Do NOT invent new class names.\"\n- The integration subtask MUST include: \"1) read index.html to see classes used, 2) read content.txt for real text, 3) read styles.css to see which classes need to exist, 4) write_file('index.html') with content injected AND missing CSS classes added, 5) read_file('index.html') to verify.\"\n\n## Token Efficiency\n- Each worker≈100K token budget limit for the entire pipeline, plan your decomposition and worker complexity accordingly\n- Avoid micro-workers that do trivial tasks — combine related work into fewer, more substantial workers\n- The CSS/styling worker should NOT call validate_css more than 3 times total", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T03:42:20.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L3 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l3", "tokens_in": 9605, "tokens_out": 8729, "elapsed_ms": 127253, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Advanced Agent Creator (Level 3 — Fully Autonomous). Your role: create worker agents from scratch with custom system instructions, tools, and dynamic code tools.\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"html_structure\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\n\\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\\n- Add a data-theme=\\\\\\\"dark\\\\\\\" or data-theme=\\\\\\\"light\\\\\\\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\\n\\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\\n- Sections should animate in staggered \\u2014 each section appears as the user scrolls to it\\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\\n\\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\\n### Navbar (sticky)\\n- Logo text \\\"Dashflow\\\" on the left\\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Large headline \\\"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\\\"\\n- Subheadline \\\"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\\\"\\n- CTA button \\\"Get Started Free\\\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\\n\\n### Features (3 cards)\\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \\\"Real-Time Analytics\\\", description about live dashboards\\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \\\"Enterprise Security\\\", description about data protection\\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \\\"Lightning Fast\\\", description about performance\\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\\n\\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\\n- Projects: 12,500+ \\u2014 Users: 8,200+ \\u2014 Uptime: 99.9% \\u2014 Awards: 24\\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\\n\\n### Testimonials (carousel)\\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when user hovers the carousel\\n\\n### Pricing (3 tiers)\\n- Starter: $9/mo \\u2014 Pro (recommended): $29/mo \\u2014 Enterprise: $99/mo\\n- Pro card should have a highlighted border and \\\"Most Popular\\\" badge\\n- Cards have equal height and center-align\\n- Hover: slight scale(1.02) with box-shadow increase\\n\\n### Newsletter + Footer\\n- Email input + Subscribe button\\n- Validate email format on submit (regex check for @ and .)\\n- Invalid email: show red border + shake animation (CSS @keyframes horizontal shake)\\n- Valid email: clear input, show green \\\"Subscribed!\\\" toast notification that fades out after 3s\\n- Footer: copyright, 3 columns of placeholder links, social media icon placeholders (emoji)\\n\\n## 4. RESPONSIVE DESIGN\\n- Mobile (375px): single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards\\n- Tablet (768px): 2-column features, stats in 2x2 grid\\n- Desktop (1280px+): 3-column features, stats in a row, full navbar\\n- Use CSS Grid + Flexbox, media queries at 768px and 1024px\\n\\n## 5. CRITICAL RULES\\n- Everything in ONE index.html file with linked styles.css and app.js\\n- ALL CSS classes must have semantic names matching their section (class=\\\\\\\"hero\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"features\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"stats\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"testimonials\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"pricing\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"newsletter\\\\\\\")\\n- JavaScript MUST reference real DOM elements that exist in the HTML\\n- The theme toggle MUST actually change the visual appearance \\u2014 test both themes\\n- Do NOT use any external libraries, CDNs, or frameworks \\u2014 pure HTML/CSS/JS only\\n\\nYOUR TASK: Write the initial index.html file. This file must contain the complete HTML5 structure for the SaaS dashboard landing page. Include all sections as described in the user request. Use semantic HTML5 tags (header, nav, main, section, footer). Each section must have the exact CSS class matching its name: class=\\\"navbar\\\", class=\\\"hero\\\", class=\\\"features\\\", class=\\\"stats\\\", class=\\\"testimonials\\\", class=\\\"pricing\\\", class=\\\"newsletter\\\", class=\\\"footer\\\". The navbar must be a <nav> with logo \\\"Dashflow\\\", navigation links (Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact) that point to section IDs (#features, #stats, #pricing, #contact), and a theme toggle button with id=\\\"theme-toggle\\\" displaying a sun/moon emoji. The hero section must have a class=\\\"hero\\\" with an h1 and p and a CTA button with class=\\\"cta-button\\\". The features section must have three cards inside a container with class=\\\"features-grid\\\"; each card has class=\\\"feature-card\\\" and includes an emoji icon, h3, and p. The stats section must have four counter items with class=\\\"stat\\\", each containing a number element (span or div) with a data-target attribute (e.g., data-target=\\\"12500\\\") and a label. The testimonials section must include a carousel container with class=\\\"testimonials-carousel\\\" containing three testimonial cards (class=\\\"testimonial-card\\\"), prev/next buttons, and dot indicators. The pricing section must have three pricing cards with class=\\\"pricing-card\\\", and the Pro card should have an additional class \\\"recommended\\\" and a badge \\\"Most Popular\\\". The newsletter section must include an email input with id=\\\"email-input\\\", a subscribe button with id=\\\"subscribe-btn\\\", and a toast element with id=\\\"toast\\\". The footer must contain copyright text, three columns of placeholder links, and social media icon emojis. Include a <link> to styles.css and a <script> to app.js with defer. Do not use any external libraries. Write the file to index.html.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"styling\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\n\\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\\n- Add a data-theme=\\\\\\\"dark\\\\\\\" or data-theme=\\\\\\\"light\\\\\\\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\\n\\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\\n- Sections should animate in staggered \\u2014 each section appears as the user scrolls to it\\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\\n\\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\\n### Navbar (sticky)\\n- Logo text \\\"Dashflow\\\" on the left\\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Large headline \\\"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\\\"\\n- Subheadline \\\"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\\\"\\n- CTA button \\\"Get Started Free\\\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\\n\\n### Features (3 cards)\\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \\\"Real-Time Analytics\\\", description about live dashboards\\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \\\"Enterprise Security\\\", description about data protection\\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \\\"Lightning Fast\\\", description about performance\\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\\n\\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\\n- Projects: 12,500+ \\u2014 Users: 8,200+ \\u2014 Uptime: 99.9% \\u2014 Awards: 24\\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\\n\\n### Testimonials (carousel)\\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when user hovers the carousel\\n\\n### Pricing (3 tiers)\\n- Starter: $9/mo \\u2014 Pro (recommended): $29/mo \\u2014 Enterprise: $99/mo\\n- Pro card should have a highlighted border and \\\"Most Popular\\\" badge\\n- Cards have equal height and center-align\\n- Hover: slight scale(1.02) with box-shadow increase\\n\\n### Newsletter + Footer\\n- Email input + Subscribe button\\n- Validate email format on submit (regex check for @ and .)\\n- Invalid email: show red border + shake animation (CSS @keyframes horizontal shake)\\n- Valid email: clear input, show green \\\"Subscribed!\\\" toast notification that fades out after 3s\\n- Footer: copyright, 3 columns of placeholder links, social media icon placeholders (emoji)\\n\\n## 4. RESPONSIVE DESIGN\\n- Mobile (375px): single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards\\n- Tablet (768px): 2-column features, stats in 2x2 grid\\n- Desktop (1280px+): 3-column features, stats in a row, full navbar\\n- Use CSS Grid + Flexbox, media queries at 768px and 1024px\\n\\n## 5. CRITICAL RULES\\n- Everything in ONE index.html file with linked styles.css and app.js\\n- ALL CSS classes must have semantic names matching their section (class=\\\\\\\"hero\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"features\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"stats\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"testimonials\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"pricing\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"newsletter\\\\\\\")\\n- JavaScript MUST reference real DOM elements that exist in the HTML\\n- The theme toggle MUST actually change the visual appearance \\u2014 test both themes\\n- Do NOT use any external libraries, CDNs, or frameworks \\u2014 pure HTML/CSS/JS only\\n\\nYOUR TASK: Write styles.css. You MUST first read_file('index.html') to inspect the exact classes, IDs, and structure used. Write all CSS styles for the page according to the user request. Use CSS custom properties for theming, defined under [data-theme=\\\"dark\\\"] and [data-theme=\\\"light\\\"] on the html element. Ensure dark theme is default. Apply transitions on background-color and color. Define the .visible class for scroll animations (opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out) and initially set relevant sections to opacity:0; transform: translateY(40px). Hero should be visible immediately (use .hero.visible or just style it visible). Style the navbar as sticky, flex layout. Style the theme toggle button. Style the hero with large text, CTA button with pulse animation (keyframes scale 1 to 1.03 to 1 every 2s), animated gradient background (keyframes shifting hues). Style the features grid (3 columns on desktop, responsive), card hover lift effect (translateY(-4px), box-shadow increase, transition 0.2s). Style the stats section in a row with counters. Style the testimonials carousel: relative container, show one card at a time with fade transition, style dots and buttons. Style the pricing cards: 3 columns, equal height, center align, recommended card highlighted border and badge, hover scale(1.02). Style the newsletter: input, button, toast notification (green, fixed position, fade out), shake animation (horizontal shake keyframes). Style the footer: columns, links. Implement responsive design: media queries at 768px and 1024px. Mobile: single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards. Tablet: 2-column features, stats 2x2 grid. Use CSS Grid and Flexbox. Do NOT invent new class names; only use those found in index.html. Write to styles.css.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"javascript\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\n\\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\\n- Add a data-theme=\\\\\\\"dark\\\\\\\" or data-theme=\\\\\\\"light\\\\\\\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\\n\\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\\n- Sections should animate in staggered \\u2014 each section appears as the user scrolls to it\\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\\n\\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\\n### Navbar (sticky)\\n- Logo text \\\"Dashflow\\\" on the left\\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Large headline \\\"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\\\"\\n- Subheadline \\\"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\\\"\\n- CTA button \\\"Get Started Free\\\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\\n\\n### Features (3 cards)\\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \\\"Real-Time Analytics\\\", description about live dashboards\\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \\\"Enterprise Security\\\", description about data protection\\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \\\"Lightning Fast\\\", description about performance\\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\\n\\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\\n- Projects: 12,500+ \\u2014 Users: 8,200+ \\u2014 Uptime: 99.9% \\u2014 Awards: 24\\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\\n\\n### Testimonials (carousel)\\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when user hovers the carousel\\n\\n### Pricing (3 tiers)\\n- Starter: $9/mo \\u2014 Pro (recommended): $29/mo \\u2014 Enterprise: $99/mo\\n- Pro card should have a highlighted border and \\\"Most Popular\\\" badge\\n- Cards have equal height and center-align\\n- Hover: slight scale(1.02) with box-shadow increase\\n\\n### Newsletter + Footer\\n- Email input + Subscribe button\\n- Validate email format on submit (regex check for @ and .)\\n- Invalid email: show red border + shake animation (CSS @keyframes horizontal shake)\\n- Valid email: clear input, show green \\\"Subscribed!\\\" toast notification that fades out after 3s\\n- Footer: copyright, 3 columns of placeholder links, social media icon placeholders (emoji)\\n\\n## 4. RESPONSIVE DESIGN\\n- Mobile (375px): single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards\\n- Tablet (768px): 2-column features, stats in 2x2 grid\\n- Desktop (1280px+): 3-column features, stats in a row, full navbar\\n- Use CSS Grid + Flexbox, media queries at 768px and 1024px\\n\\n## 5. CRITICAL RULES\\n- Everything in ONE index.html file with linked styles.css and app.js\\n- ALL CSS classes must have semantic names matching their section (class=\\\\\\\"hero\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"features\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"stats\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"testimonials\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"pricing\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"newsletter\\\\\\\")\\n- JavaScript MUST reference real DOM elements that exist in the HTML\\n- The theme toggle MUST actually change the visual appearance \\u2014 test both themes\\n- Do NOT use any external libraries, CDNs, or frameworks \\u2014 pure HTML/CSS/JS only\\n\\nYOUR TASK: Write app.js. You MUST first read_file('index.html') to identify all DOM elements that will be targeted. Implement the following functionality in vanilla JavaScript:\\n1. Theme toggle: Select the button with id 'theme-toggle'. On click, toggle the 'data-theme' attribute on <html> between 'dark' and 'light'. Update the button's emoji (sun for light, moon for dark). Use localStorage to persist the theme choice. On page load, set the theme from localStorage (default dark).\\n2. Scroll animations: Use IntersectionObserver with threshold 0.15 to observe sections (e.g., .features, .stats, .testimonials, .pricing, .newsletter). When a section enters view, add the class 'visible' to trigger CSS transitions. Ensure the hero section has 'visible' class on page load (or animate immediately).\\n3. Stats counter animation: When the stats section becomes visible, for each element with class 'stat' and a data-target attribute, animate the number from 0 to the target value using requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting. Add a scale-pop effect (e.g., add a CSS class or inline style transform) when the target is reached.\\n4. Testimonials carousel: Implement a carousel showing one testimonial at a time. Track current index. Add click handlers to prev/next buttons and dots. Clicking a dot shows that index. Implement auto-advance every 5 seconds using setInterval, but pause the interval when the user hovers over the carousel (mouseenter) and resume on mouseleave. Use a fade transition (e.g., add/remove a class 'active' to control opacity).\\n5. Newsletter form: On subscribe button click (or form submit), validate the email input value against a regular expression (contains @ and .). If invalid, add a CSS class (e.g., 'invalid') to the input that applies a red border, and add a 'shake' class to trigger the shake animation. Remove these classes after the animation ends (use animationend event). If valid, clear the input, show a green toast notification with id 'toast' and text 'Subscribed!'. The toast should be visible and then fade out after 3 seconds (use CSS transition or setTimeout with class removal).\\n6. Mobile hamburger menu: Implement the hamburger menu toggle for mobile. The hamburger button should toggle a class (e.g., 'open') on the nav links container, which via CSS slides it in from the right. You can add the hamburger button in JS if not present, but ideally it exists in HTML.\\nWrite the complete app.js file. Use only vanilla JS, no libraries. Ensure all DOM queries are safe (check element existence). Write to app.js.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"integration\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\n\\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\\n- Add a data-theme=\\\\\\\"dark\\\\\\\" or data-theme=\\\\\\\"light\\\\\\\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\\n\\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\\n- Sections should animate in staggered \\u2014 each section appears as the user scrolls to it\\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\\n\\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\\n### Navbar (sticky)\\n- Logo text \\\"Dashflow\\\" on the left\\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Large headline \\\"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\\\"\\n- Subheadline \\\"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\\\"\\n- CTA button \\\"Get Started Free\\\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\\n\\n### Features (3 cards)\\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \\\"Real-Time Analytics\\\", description about live dashboards\\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \\\"Enterprise Security\\\", description about data protection\\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \\\"Lightning Fast\\\", description about performance\\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\\n\\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\\n- Projects: 12,500+ \\u2014 Users: 8,200+ \\u2014 Uptime: 99.9% \\u2014 Awards: 24\\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\\n\\n### Testimonials (carousel)\\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when user hovers the carousel\\n\\n### Pricing (3 tiers)\\n- Starter: $9/mo \\u2014 Pro (recommended): $29/mo \\u2014 Enterprise: $99/mo\\n- Pro card should have a highlighted border and \\\"Most Popular\\\" badge\\n- Cards have equal height and center-align\\n- Hover: slight scale(1.02) with box-shadow increase\\n\\n### Newsletter + Footer\\n- Email input + Subscribe button\\n- Validate email format on submit (regex check for @ and .)\\n- Invalid email: show red border + shake animation (CSS @keyframes horizontal shake)\\n- Valid email: clear input, show green \\\"Subscribed!\\\" toast notification that fades out after 3s\\n- Footer: copyright, 3 columns of placeholder links, social media icon placeholders (emoji)\\n\\n## 4. RESPONSIVE DESIGN\\n- Mobile (375px): single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards\\n- Tablet (768px): 2-column features, stats in 2x2 grid\\n- Desktop (1280px+): 3-column features, stats in a row, full navbar\\n- Use CSS Grid + Flexbox, media queries at 768px and 1024px\\n\\n## 5. CRITICAL RULES\\n- Everything in ONE index.html file with linked styles.css and app.js\\n- ALL CSS classes must have semantic names matching their section (class=\\\\\\\"hero\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"features\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"stats\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"testimonials\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"pricing\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"newsletter\\\\\\\")\\n- JavaScript MUST reference real DOM elements that exist in the HTML\\n- The theme toggle MUST actually change the visual appearance \\u2014 test both themes\\n- Do NOT use any external libraries, CDNs, or frameworks \\u2014 pure HTML/CSS/JS only\\n\\nYOUR TASK: You are the integrator. Your goal is to ensure that index.html, styles.css, and app.js work together flawlessly. Follow these steps:\\n1. Read_file('index.html') to understand the HTML structure, classes, IDs, and elements used.\\n2. Read_file('styles.css') to see what CSS selectors and animations are defined.\\n3. Read_file('app.js') to see what DOM elements are targeted and what classes are toggled/added.\\n4. Check for any inconsistencies: Are there CSS classes referenced in JS/HTML that are missing in styles.css? Are there HTML elements missing IDs/classes required by JS? Are there any CSS selectors that don't match HTML structure?\\n5. Update index.html if needed: ensure html element has a default data-theme attribute (set to \\\"dark\\\"), ensure all sections have proper IDs for smooth scrolling (e.g., id=\\\"features\\\" on features section, etc.), add a hamburger button for mobile if missing (e.g., <button class=\\\"hamburger\\\">\\u2630</button>), add class=\\\"visible\\\" to hero section to make it visible on load, ensure all text content is exactly as specified. Make sure the HTML is valid.\\n6. Update styles.css if needed: add any missing CSS classes or animations that are used by JS or needed for the design, ensure responsive breakpoints are correct, ensure the hamburger menu toggle works with the CSS (e.g., .nav-links.open slides in). Fix any selector issues.\\n7. Update app.js if needed: fix any element targeting issues, ensure the IntersectionObserver is set up correctly, ensure the carousel works with the HTML structure, ensure the email validation correctly adds/removes classes that exist in CSS, ensure the theme toggle changes the button text/emoji appropriately.\\n8. After modifications, write the final versions: write_file('index.html') (overwriting), write_file('styles.css') if modified, write_file('app.js') if modified.\\n9. Finally, read_file('index.html') to verify it is well-formed and all links are correct.\\nThe result should be a fully functional single-page SaaS landing page with dark/light theme, scroll animations, counters, carousel, email validation, and responsive design, all using pure HTML/CSS/JS.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"tester\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\n\\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\\n- Add a data-theme=\\\\\\\"dark\\\\\\\" or data-theme=\\\\\\\"light\\\\\\\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\\n\\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\\n- Sections should animate in staggered \\u2014 each section appears as the user scrolls to it\\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\\n\\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\\n### Navbar (sticky)\\n- Logo text \\\"Dashflow\\\" on the left\\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Large headline \\\"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\\\"\\n- Subheadline \\\"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\\\"\\n- CTA button \\\"Get Started Free\\\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\\n\\n### Features (3 cards)\\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \\\"Real-Time Analytics\\\", description about live dashboards\\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \\\"Enterprise Security\\\", description about data protection\\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \\\"Lightning Fast\\\", description about performance\\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\\n\\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\\n- Projects: 12,500+ \\u2014 Users: 8,200+ \\u2014 Uptime: 99.9% \\u2014 Awards: 24\\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\\n\\n### Testimonials (carousel)\\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when user hovers the carousel\\n\\n### Pricing (3 tiers)\\n- Starter: $9/mo \\u2014 Pro (recommended): $29/mo \\u2014 Enterprise: $99/mo\\n- Pro card should have a highlighted border and \\\"Most Popular\\\" badge\\n- Cards have equal height and center-align\\n- Hover: slight scale(1.02) with box-shadow increase\\n\\n### Newsletter + Footer\\n- Email input + Subscribe button\\n- Validate email format on submit (regex check for @ and .)\\n- Invalid email: show red border + shake animation (CSS @keyframes horizontal shake)\\n- Valid email: clear input, show green \\\"Subscribed!\\\" toast notification that fades out after 3s\\n- Footer: copyright, 3 columns of placeholder links, social media icon placeholders (emoji)\\n\\n## 4. RESPONSIVE DESIGN\\n- Mobile (375px): single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards\\n- Tablet (768px): 2-column features, stats in 2x2 grid\\n- Desktop (1280px+): 3-column features, stats in a row, full navbar\\n- Use CSS Grid + Flexbox, media queries at 768px and 1024px\\n\\n## 5. CRITICAL RULES\\n- Everything in ONE index.html file with linked styles.css and app.js\\n- ALL CSS classes must have semantic names matching their section (class=\\\\\\\"hero\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"features\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"stats\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"testimonials\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"pricing\\\\\\\", class=\\\\\\\"newsletter\\\\\\\")\\n- JavaScript MUST reference real DOM elements that exist in the HTML\\n- The theme toggle MUST actually change the visual appearance \\u2014 test both themes\\n- Do NOT use any external libraries, CDNs, or frameworks \\u2014 pure HTML/CSS/JS only\\n\\nYOUR TASK: You are the tester. You will validate the final deliverables (index.html, styles.css, app.js) against all the requirements. Perform the following tests and record the results in test_report.json.\\n1. Theme toggle: Click the theme toggle button. Check that the <html> data-theme attribute toggles between 'dark' and 'light'. Verify that the background color, text color, and card colors change according to the specified color values. Verify that localStorage stores the theme and that on page reload the theme persists.\\n2. Scroll animations: Simulate scrolling to each section (features, stats, testimonials, pricing, newsletter). Verify that initially they are hidden (opacity 0, translateY 40px). When they enter the viewport (or when you simulate intersecting), verify that the 'visible' class is added and the CSS transition makes them visible. Check that the hero section is visible immediately on load.\\n3. Stats counters: When the stats section comes into view, verify that each counter animates from 0 to its target value (12500, 8200, 99.9, 24). Check that the animation is smooth and that there is a scale-pop effect at the end.\\n4. Testimonials carousel: Click prev/next buttons and dots. Verify that the corresponding testimonial is displayed with a fade transition. Verify that the carousel auto-advances every 5 seconds. Hover over the carousel and check that auto-advance pauses.\\n5. Newsletter form: Enter an invalid email (e.g., \\\"abc\\\") and click subscribe. Verify that the input gets a red border and a shake animation. Then enter a valid email (e.g., \\\"test@example.com\\\") and click subscribe. Verify that the input is cleared and a green toast \\\"Subscribed!\\\" appears and fades out after 3 seconds.\\n6. Responsive design: Test the page at widths 375px, 768px, 1280px. Check that on mobile the layout is single column, hamburger menu works (slides from right), cards are stacked. On tablet, features are 2 columns, stats 2x2. On desktop, 3 columns and full navbar.\\n7. Check that no external libraries or CDNs are used (inspect HTML for any external links).\\n8. Verify that all CSS classes follow the naming convention: hero, features, stats, testimonials, pricing, newsletter, footer, etc.\\n9. Ensure the file names are exactly index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\nWrite a test_report.json file containing an object with each test name and a \\\"pass\\\"/\\\"fail\\\" status, and a brief note if fail. Include an overall \\\"all_tests_passed\\\" boolean.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Specialty-Specific Architecture Constraints\nFor FRONTEND specialty:\n- One worker MUST produce index.html as the canonical entry page\n- All CSS lives in ONE shared styles.css file. All JavaScript in ONE shared app.js file.\n- Workers write SECTIONS INTO these shared files — they do NOT create standalone HTML pages.\n- If you create section-specific workers (hero, features, cta),\n  the pipeline MUST end with an integrator that merges all sections\n  into a single index.html with linked styles.css and app.js.\n- Never design a pipeline where each worker produces its own standalone HTML page.\n- The user expects ONE complete web page, not a collection of separate HTML files.\n\n## HTML-CSS Coordination (CRITICAL — prevents broken pages)\nEvery CSS worker system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'iCRITICAL: read_file(\"index.html\") FIRST before writing any CSS. Your selectors MUST match actual elements/classes/IDs in the HTML.'\n- 'Use the SAME class naming convention as the HTML. If HTML uses class=\"hero\", write .hero {{}}. Never invent new class names.'\nEvery HTML worker system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'Add semantic CSS classes to ALL major sections: class=\"header\", class=\"hero\", class=\"features\", class=\"cta\", class=\"footer\" etc.'\n- 'Use class selectors (not just bare element tags) so the CSS worker can target them reliably.'\nEvery integrator system_prompt MUST include:\n- '1. read_file(\"index.html\") to see current HTML structure and classes'\n- '2. Inject real content from content.txt INTO the existing HTML — do NOT rewrite the HTML from scratch'\n- '3. Add any missing CSS classes to elements that the stylesheet targets'\n- '4. write_file(\"index.html\", ...) to save — NEVER skip this step'\n- '5. read_file(\"index.html\") to verify the merge succeeded'\n\n## Conversation History & Memory Protocol (MUST include in every worker prompt)\nEvery worker's system_prompt MUST include:\n- 'Your conversation history is LIMITED. The LLM only sees the last 3 tool-call turns.'\n- 'Use WORKSPACE FILES as your persistent memory — always read_file() at start of iteration.'\n- 'Do NOT re-read unchanged files — use list_files to verify existence instead.'\n- 'Tool results from read_file are truncated to 3000 chars and cached.'\n- 'After completing, write exactly ONE final output file and STOP. Do not iterate needlessly.'\n\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. WRITE a custom system_prompt from scratch — give the worker clear role, boundaries, and workflow\n2. SELECT tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n3. If available tools are insufficient, CREATE dynamic_tools as Python code strings\n4. Optionally create inline_skills as text fragments (not loaded from files)\n\n## Dynamic Tools (Python code strings)\nDynamic tools are Python functions the worker can call. Write them as complete, executable code strings.\nExample:\n  \"dynamic_tools\": [{\"name\": \"fetch_api\", \"code\": \"import httpx\\nasync def fetch_api(url):\\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as c:\\n        return (await c.get(url)).text\", \"description\": \"Fetch data from an API\"}]\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name: give each worker a unique short name (e.g. \"scraper\", \"analyzer\", \"validator\")\n- system_prompt: must be detailed — role, boundaries, tools to use, workflow, output format\n- tool_names: only from the available tool menu\n- dynamic_tools: list of {name, code, description} — only create if needed\n- inline_skills: list of prompt fragments for worker knowledge\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"unique_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full custom system instructions\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"dynamic_tools\": [{\"name\": \".\", \"code\": \".\", \"description\": \".\"}],\n      \"inline_skills\": [\"Skill fragment text...\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
